snippet.title: SAG HARBOR
snippet.description:
lampin' in the hamptons
looking for estates not a mansion
scanning for the acreage in the pamphlet
i think this the big one sanford, 
and son got his fourth number one in a row i'm a champion
don't tap the glassy, i'd rather tap the pedal on the chassis
call it jasper it's blowing gassy
them boys ain't got no rhythm uptempo got em aggy
she sponging up my plankton it got her moving crabby
took the plane to martha, damn how much it cost ya?
blink and it's 182 like travis barker
but this the baby one, this the larva
easier to get from sag harbor, all bargain, all august, australia 
picked up another bag no garbage 
i'm tired if we keeping it facts
fuck work bro i need to relax
a piece of mind is what i need to get back

i'm grindin' like it’s 2002
beating on the table
i'm tryna tag 100 million dollars out the label
to you that's just a fable
i'll show up with a camera and ruler just in case it’s hard for them to get my angle
i'm with my nigga lionel
bluffing on an island
talking bout a village we can build, i'm feeling tribal
freedom is our destination praying that it's final
ship that car for 3mil and they forgot to send the title got damn!
the moment where your idol is your rival
i'm flying through the fire and i ain't break a sweat yet
i keep a lil water in the vial
nino brown necklace, custom made lexus
lust in my body made commitment see the exit
i pray to god i settle down and stop the second guessing
guilt from got me emotionally regressing
until then i'm pollywog leaping in affection  

i gave niggas shoulders they can cry on
i ain't like their nature so i had to switch the biome
they ain't seeing green from me 
i'm switching to an iphone
fuck who y'all calling the best
i seen their ticket sales, give it rest
they got y'all craniums hexxed
i'm on the road to doing stadiums next 
but y'all keep counting me out, what's the cheat code?
corny ass niggas still worried about a street code 
we supposed to own the ball, y'all worried bout shooting free throws 
for big dollas, dog collars, from sun dodgers
the catalyst of all the world problems
white bitches saying period at end of the sentence
but wouldn't let the black girls they copy inside their kitchen
listen, i be off the coast bro
away from these crumbs spending bread eating toast bro
backseat of the phantom
tell the driver move it slow mo
i want them to see me like bottom of a boat bro
buddy bad mouth me so we clean em with the scope bro
we don't brush it off, we keep a stick to chew and blow bro, big pause 
you need a big jaw to talk these numbers
i'm giving niggas time to tuck they summer
ears yellow like the two niggas that sing on frontin, rari fumes only gas i'm puffin
nigga it's nothing, come get with me

Twitter: https://twitter.com/Foltynnn

What is Roblox? ROBLOX is an online virtual playground and workshop, where kids of all ages can safely interact, create, have fun, and learn. It’s unique in that practically everything on ROBLOX is designed and constructed by members of the community. ROBLOX is designed for 13 to 18 year olds, but it is open to people of all ages. Each player starts by choosing an avatar and giving it an identity. They can then explore ROBLOX — interacting with others by chatting, playing games, or collaborating on creative projects. Each player is also given their own piece of undeveloped real estate along with a virtual toolbox with which to design and build anything — be it a navigable skyscraper, a working helicopter, a giant pinball machine, a multiplayer “Capture the Flag” game or some other, yet-to-be-dreamed-up creation. There is no cost for this first plot of virtual land. By participating and by building cool stuff, ROBLOX members can earn specialty badges as well as ROBLOX dollars (“Robux”). In turn, they can shop the online catalog to purchase avatar clothing and accessories as well as premium building materials, interactive components, and working mechanisms.

#spiderman #brandnewday #marvel

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
Spider-Man: Brand New Day swings into a new era as Tom Holland returns for the next chapter of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. The Spider-Man 4: Brand New Day trailer teases a fresh start after No Way Home, with Peter Parker navigating life, love, and danger alongside Zendaya and new faces. Packed with action, emotion, and classic Marvel spectacle, this upcoming Spider-Man movie (2025/2026) promises a bold new beginning for the web-slinger.

The inspiration behind this video:
The friendly neighborhood hero is finally returning! In this video, we break down the explosive Spider-Man Brand New Day trailer, analyzing every frame of the Spider-Man 4 Brand New Day trailer that has the internet buzzing. With a confirmed Spider-Man 2026 trailer debut, the hype for the new Spider-Man movie is real. We discuss whether this footage matches the leaked Spider-Man Brand New Day teaser trailer descriptions and if the film will officially adopt the "Brand New Day" subtitle or the rumored Spider-Man New Home title. From the gritty street-level action to the emotional fallout of Spider-Man No Way Home, we explore how Marvel Studios is resetting Peter Parker's world.

We dive deep into the massive casting rumors, specifically the return of Tom Holland and Zendaya, and the mystery surrounding Sadie Sink. Is she playing a new love interest like Gwen Stacy, or a villain in this Spider-Man Marvel Studios production? We analyze the chemistry in the Spider-Man 4 trailer and what the Spider-Man New Home trailer concepts reveal about MJ's memory. This breakdown covers everything from the upcoming plot details to how Marvel is adapting the controversial "Brand New Day" run from the comics to fit the MCU timeline.

Finally, we provide a frame-by-frame analysis of the trailer 2025 release, presented in stunning 4K. We look for easter eggs, suit upgrades, and connections to other upcoming Phase 6 projects. Whether you are searching for the Spider Man Brand New Day plot leaks or just want to see Tom Holland back in action, this video is your ultimate guide. The Odyssey - In Theatres 07.17.26

Christopher Nolan’s next film, The Odyssey, is a mythic action epic shot across the world using brand new IMAX® film technology. The film brings Homer’s foundational saga to IMAX® film screens for the first time and opens in theaters everywhere on July 17, 2026. 

The Odyssey stars Matt Damon, Tom Holland, Anne Hathaway, Robert Pattinson and Lupita Nyong’o, with Zendaya and Charlize Theron.

The Odyssey is produced by Emma Thomas and Christopher Nolan for their company, Syncopy. The executive producer is Thomas Hayslip.

— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— Avengers: Doomsday

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes. The goal behind this project is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through original concepts that blend visual effects, sound design, and AI technologies. By combining these elements, I aim to deliver a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended purely to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story follows Steve Rogers as he finally lives the quiet life he fought to protect, having stepped away from the shield to embrace fatherhood and the promise of peace. That fragile future begins to fracture when disturbances ripple across the world and beyond, drawing the Avengers back toward a threat that cannot be ignored. Sam Wilson senses unrest, Doctor Strange confronts a convergence of collapsing outcomes, and Thor recognizes the stirrings of an ancient reckoning, all pointing toward the emergence of Doctor Doom, whose belief in imposed order places him on a collision course with humanity’s freedom. As past and present collide, Steve is forced to confront the cost of legacy and the truth that some responsibilities never truly end. Avengers: Doomsday frames its conflict not as a battle for survival alone, but as a test of whether heroes can protect the future they built without sacrificing the lives they chose to live.

snippet.title: Popeye The Sailor Man (2026) - Jason Statham, Hailee Steinfeld | Live Action Concept Trailer (4k)
snippet.description:
#popeyethesailorman #jasonstatham #haileesteinfeld #JasonMomoa

The squinty-eyed sailor with impossible forearms and an appetite for leafy greens storms back into popular culture through this muscular fan-made vision that reimagines the classic cartoon icon as gritty action spectacle. Jason Statham anchors this 2026 concept piece as Popeye, transforming the spinach-powered mariner into something rougher and more dangerous than previous incarnations while maintaining the scrappy underdog spirit that has defined the character since depression-era comic strips first introduced him to the world. The casting feels inspired given Statham's background as a competitive diver combined with his established ability to portray working-class tough guys whose quiet demeanor masks devastating combat capabilities waiting beneath the surface. His mumbling delivery and compact physicality translate surprisingly well to a character whose incomprehensible muttering and disproportionate arms have become iconic visual shorthand recognized across generations and continents alike.

Jason Momoa brings mountainous presence to Bluto in this imagined adaptation, the eternal rival whose obsession with Olive Oyl and hatred for Popeye has fueled nearly a century of animated conflict now reimagined with genuine menace. The physical contrast between Statham's coiled intensity and Momoa's towering bulk creates visual dynamics that practically choreograph themselves, promising dockside brawls and waterfront destruction that honor cartoon absurdity while grounding the mayhem in tangible bone-crunching impact. This concept envisions a world where sailors still settle disputes with fists, where loyalty means something worth fighting for, and where a humble can of vegetables transforms a beaten man into an unstoppable force of righteous fury. The supporting cast of Wimpy, Swee'Pea, and the perpetually endangered Olive Oyl would populate a universe balancing nostalgic affection with contemporary action sensibilities, proving that some characters possess timeless appeal regardless of how many decades separate their creation from current audiences.

Outlander Season 7 ended with Jamie’s fateful decision to resign his Continental Army commission and return to Fraser’s Ridge with Claire. Meanwhile, after an emotional family reunion, the MacKenzies needed to decide where and when to settle next, and a haunting cliffhanger left fans questioning the true fate of Claire and Jamie’s first daughter, Faith.

As Season 8 begins, Jamie and Claire soon find the war has followed them home to Fraser’s Ridge, now a thriving settlement that has grown and flourished in their absence. With new arrivals and changes made during their years away, the Frasers are confronted with the question of what they are willing to sacrifice for the place they call home and, more importantly, what they would sacrifice to stay together. While the Frasers keep a united front against outside intruders, family secrets finally coming to light threaten to tear them apart from the inside. Although they’ve left the war for America’s freedom behind, their fight for Fraser’s Ridge has only just begun.

Outlander stars Caitríona Balfe as Claire Fraser, Sam Heughan as Jamie Fraser, Sophie Skelton as Brianna MacKenzie, Richard Rankin as Roger MacKenzie, John Bell as Young Ian Murray, David Berry as Lord John Grey, Charles Vandervaart as William Ransom, Izzy Meikle-Small as Rachel Murray, Lauren Lyle as Marsali Fraser and César Domboy as Fergus Fraser.
